The paper deals with the problem of sorting a set given partial information, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of graph entropy and information theory suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The development of efficient algorithms involves the use of approximation techniques and optimization, which are common in computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of entropy and graph theory also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
